`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
The input system test suite is a good example of **layered testing strategy**: `InputManager.test.ts` tests the merge/normalization logic in pure TS (no DOM needed), while `KeyboardMouseProvider.test.ts` and `TouchProvider.test.ts` use `@jest-environment jsdom` only where browser APIs are required. This minimizes the overhead of DOM environment setup to only the files that need it.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

US-028 is already complete. All 64 tests across the three input system test files pass:

- `InputManager.test.ts` — 9 tests: frame shape, provider merging, unit-circle clamping, OR booleans, first-wins toolSwap, disabled/unregistered providers
- `KeyboardMouseProvider.test.ts` — 28 tests: WASD/arrows, opposing key cancel, edge-triggered actions, pointer lock guard, delta accumulation, postFrame reset
- `TouchProvider.test.ts` — 27 tests: joystick direction/clamping, onTouchMove/End lifecycle, viewport swipe look, multi-touch isolation, action buttons, isAvailable, dispose

Both `npx tsc --noEmit` and `npx jest --no-coverage` pass cleanly.

